-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/japan-s-kddi-to-replace-up-to-2-million-handset-batteries-on-overheating.html
KDDI Corp. (9433)  will replace as many as
2 million batteries in three Japanese mobile handset models made
by  Hitachi Ltd. (6501)  and Casio Computer Co. due to concerns the
batteries may overheat.  The company received eight reports of the batteries
overheating, according to a statement on its website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
